item.title: CVE-2023-33236|2024-08-02T15:39:35.839Z -- moxa -- mxsecurity%20series
item.description: MXsecurity version 1.0 is vulnearble to hardcoded credential vulnerability. This vulnerability has been reported that can be exploited to craft arbitrary JWT tokens and subsequently bypass authentication for web-based APIs.

item.title: CVE-2023-33235|2024-08-02T15:39:35.741Z -- moxa -- mxsecurity%20series
item.description: MXsecurity version 1.0 is vulnearble to command injection vulnerability. This vulnerability has been reported in the SSH CLI program, which can be exploited by attackers who have gained authorization privileges. The attackers can break out of the restricted shell and subsequently execute arbitrary code.
